  {
    "type": "list",
    "content": [
      "Want to participate in Isfeld's Talent show in late May? See the posters around the school for a QR code for audition information!",
      "Clothing Swap!!- Are you looking to revamp your style but don't want to spend the money? You can bring clothes that you no longer wear to Kyla's office in Student Services between April 30th and May 2nd at 2:30 and receive one ticket per item of clothing. Then on May 3rd from 3-6pm at the LINC you can trade one ticket for one item of clothing. For example, if you have 8 tickets you can get 8 items of clothing. If you have any questions don't hesitate to drop by Kyla's office.",
      "Are you a grade 11 or 12 student interested in the health field but don't know where to start? Then this is the presentation for you! On May 27th Guess my job Health will have 8-9 panelists who work in our local hospital in various departments. You will have an opportunity to ask questions to those in the field and learn about various careers. Cost $10. Location is GP Vanier. Come to the Careers office to register."
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "list",
    "content": [
      "Youth Work in Trades - are you connected to someone in a trade - a family member, friend, or local business who could apprentice you? If so, you might be eligible for the Youth Work in Trades program! Start your apprenticeship while still in school, earn 16 high school credits (Just for working), gain paid work experience, and log hours toward your trade certification. Students who report 900+ hours may even qualify for a $1000 award! Learn more: comoxvalleyschools.ca/career-programs/youth-work-in-trades or contact Tammy Williamson at tammy.williamson@sd71.bc.ca",
      "Careers information opportunity for grade 10-12. If you are interested in a career within the Natural Resource Sector this is the opportunity for you. Interactive Natural Resources Expo put on by WorkBC. Timberline High School. Friday May 9. 10:30am-1:00pm. Students will be bused to Timberline Secondary School to take part. To register please come to the Careers office.",
      "FIRST AID CERTIFICATION - is being offered on Tuesday May 27th. Cost is $60. If you want to register please come to the Careers office.",
      "Want a summer job at Crown Isle? - Various positions for aged 16 year and over, no experience necessary. For more info e-mail John Landry jlandry@crownisle.ca.",
      "Careers in Natural Resource Expo - on May 9th you can sign up to join us at the Careers in Natural Resource Expo, at Timberline Secondary School. This is a full day event and cost $10. Please come to the Careers office to register as spots are limited.",
      "Healthcare field opportunity - the Step Up Youth Program is an Island-wide program that offers Vancouver Island youth aged 15 to 18 the opportunity to volunteer at select Island Health hospitals and long-term care homes. From September to April each year, Step Up Youth volunteers provide social engagement support to patients and residents during after-school shifts at local healthcare facilities. The program introduces and promotes Island Health's C.A.R.E. values and fosters responsibility, compassion, and leadership development. Volunteers enrich the experience of patients and residents through the gift of time, empathy, and companionship. Volunteers also participate in a virtual monthly Guest Speaker series and are eligible to apply for Scholarships and Bursaries offered by Island Health. Applications are open until May 15. Visit www.islandhealth.ca/stepupyouth or email stepupyouth@islandhealth.ca"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "list",
    "content": [
      "Scholarship Opportunity for Grade 12's! A new scholarship program for people looking to pursue a career in the building materials industry, in a variety of roles. The Supply-Build Canada Rising Star Awards, presented by Star Building Materials, a Qualico Company provides 4 scholarships of $5,000 each to those facing economic barriers to education with one created for Women, one for Newcomers to Canada, and one for Indigenous Peoples. For more information or for an application, visit Scholarship Deadline Calendar under the Grad tab on our website. Deadline to apply is May 1, 2025."
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "list",
    "content": [
      "A gentle reminder that students must be in a position to graduate in order to take part in the graduation ceremony on June 14th. Please review all online courses to ensure you will earn credit by the deadline of May 30, 2025.",
      "A reminder to log in and make your Post Secondary Institution selections in the StudentTranscripts Service (STS). You will need to do this for post secondary institutions to be able to access your Transcripts. Most public BC and Alberta universities and colleges and the Ontario Universities' Application Centre (OUAC) can retrieve ongoing transcript updates as soon as authorized by the student in STS.",
      "Grade 12's attending NIC in the Fall!/Winter! An NIC Advisor will be here on Wednesday, May 14th from 9noon to support students with their program plan. Sign up in student services for your 30 minute appointment. Please note that students must have paid their tuition deposit as requested by admissions.",
      "The Grad Attire program welcomes all Gr 12 students in Comox Valley Schools to have the opportunity to wear a gown or suit on graduation day without the financial burden of purchasing a brand-new outfit for their milestone event. The Grad Attire program will operate out of Comox Valley Dodge at 278 North Island Highway (Old Canadian Tire building) on Saturday May 10th (last date) from 10:00am-3:00pm. You can book a fitting appt using the following https://www.comoxvalleyschools.ca/grad-attire-program/"
    ]
  }
